Package uk.co.saiman.data

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Calibration
    A reversible calibration or conversion between units for a ContinuousFunction domain.
    ContinuousFunction
    A set of domain values (X) mapped via some continuous function to a corresponding value in the range (Y).
    ContinuousFunctionDecorator
    A partial implementation of a ContinuousFunction decorator, to reduce boilerplate for functions which are in some way mappings of other functions.
    RegularSampledContinuousFunction
    A partial-implementation of SampledContinuousFunction with regular intervals in the domain between samples.
    SampledContinuousFunction
    A partial-implementation of ContinuousFunction for sampled continua.
    SampledContinuousFunctionDecorator
    A partial implementation of a SampledContinuousFunction decorator, to reduce boilerplate for functions which are in some way mappings of other functions.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayRegularSampledContinuousFunction
    A mutable implementation conforming to the contract of RegularSampledContinuousFunction and backed by an array.
    ArraySampledContinuousFunction
    A mutable, array backed implementation of SampledContinuousFunction.
    CalibratedContinuousFunction
    An implementation of SampledContinuousFunction which maps from another SampledContinuousFunction by some Calibration.
    ContinuousFunctionExpression
    A basic wrapper around another continuous function which reflects all changes in that function, and propagates events to listeners.
    ContinuousFunctionTransformation
    A ContinuousFunction which is backed by a given ContinuousFunction and which is derived from it by a given transformation function.
    SampledContinuousFunctionTransformation
    A SampledContinuousFunction which is backed by a given ContinuousFunction and which is derived from it by a given transformation function.
    SparseSampledContinuousFunction
    A (currently) immutable implementation of RegularSampledContinuousFunction which optimises memory usage for sampled continua with mostly 0 sample values in the codomain.
